commitResults.messageTitle: Duke.java: replace original greeting with ThawBot greeting
Add Echo for level 1 Increment This commit does the following: *Adds a feature where the program repeat the user's input *Adds a feature that will allow the user to manually exit the program

Edit Echo by adding List for level 2 increment This commit does the following: *Adds a new command "list" that displays all the previously typed texts by the user *Adds a feature where every line of texts entered by user is stored
Add "mark as done" feature for level 3 increment Add Task class that replaces the original list of strings that contains the user inputs

Level 4 Increment Add support for tracking three types of tasks: ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it e.g., visit new theme park Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time e.g., submit report by 11/10/2019 5pm Events: tasks that start at a specific date/time and ends at a specific date/time
fix: bug#1 Bug is printing the type of task like todo, event and deadline when the bot respond to you after adding a task. E.g. "[][] todo read book" instead of "'[][] read book
Add Level 5 increment This commit contains the error exception handling for invalid user inputs
Reduce code length for most of the functions
Merge branch 'branch-Level-5'
Use Java Collection class ArrayList
Add support for deleting tasks from the list
Add file loading when bot comes online
Implement loading from saved data
Add level-7 increment Implement a save feature
Merge branch 'branch-Level-6'
Change ThawBot.txt

Remove content in ThawBot.txt

commitResults.messageTitle: Update gitignore to remove ThawBot.txt from version control
Refactor classes into 5 packages (for readability): * Commands package * Exception package * Filemanager package * PrintMessages package * Tasks package
Restructure the way exceptions are handled Exception is throw from the classes in the commands package instead of from main, making the code looks neater

Make the code more OOP extract the following classes: *UI: For displaying response messages from the bot *Storage: Saving and loading of files *Parser: Process user's input *TaskList: Contains the task and its operations
